  "_doc": "Phase-4c demo: REGISTER, COUNTER, SHIFT_REG side by side. Click VERILOG to see how each component lowers:\n  • REGISTER (8-bit) — `always @(posedge clk)` with CLR > EN priority chain.\n  • COUNTER (4-bit) — CLR > LOAD > EN priority chain, increment expression `(count + 4'h1)`, plus a continuous `assign tc = (&count);` (terminal count = all bits set, via Verilog's reduction AND).\n  • SHIFT_REG (4-bit, bidirectional) — DIR=1 picks `{q[N-2:0], din}` (left), DIR=0 picks `{din, q[N-1:1]}` (right). All gated by EN, all reset by CLR.\nA bug fix tucked inside this phase: COUNTER's TC output now correctly emits as a 1-bit wire instead of inheriting the parent's 4-bit width.",
